subSubSection.paragraph:
Colour in life unknown. Pigmentation of slide-mounted specimens: ANT rather uniformly brown, except sometimes base of ANT III; head and thorax dark brown; third rostral segment and URS brown; coxae and trochanters brown; femora of fore and mid legs pale brown, of hind legs darker on distal two-thirds; tibiae pale brown except towards apices, tarsi brown; 
SIPH
brown, cauda pale to mid-brown. Dorsal sclerites brown, spiracular plates and marginal sclerites dark brown.
